-- Russian economy ministry raises 2014 inflation forecast to 7.5 pct - Interfax
-- 
-- Tue Sep 16, 2014 10:43AM EDT
-- None



MOSCOW, Sept 16 (Reuters) - Russia's Economy Ministry has raised its year-end inflation forecast for 2014 to 7.5 percent from 7.2 percent, Economy Minister Alexei Ulyukayev said on Tuesday, Interfax news agency reported.

Ulyukayev said there was a risk that inflation for the year would be as high as 8 percent.